ATTACHMENT A Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Richmond Spider Solar, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
RICHMOND SPIDER SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Richmond Spider Solar, LLC ("Richmond Spider") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Richmond Spider generating facility ("Richmond Spider Facility").
The Richmond Spider Facility is a solar generating facility located in Spotsylvania County, Virginia. The Richmond Spider Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Richmond Spider's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Richmond Spider Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Richmond Spider's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Richmond Spider shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $338,197.12 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $28,183.09
